cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.RO

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the estimation of 3D body shape and pose from camera views. Additionally, it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves volumetric reconstruction of human performance. The use of deep learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the method in on-set and prosumer scenarios suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
